<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Photo, Wintering Hole: Canada geese fly over and feed near the Sepulveda Basin 
wildlife lake, which is being filled with half a foot of water this week so 
migratory fowl can use it as a resting place for the winter. The 10-acre lake 
near Woodley Avenue and Burbank Boulevard has blinds, such as the one below, 
for bird-watchers. The lake was to be filled this fall, but an engineering 
mistake delayed the project. The lake bottom was dug too deep to drain properly 
and had to be regraded at a cost of about $45,000, said Gary Schussolin, a city 
parks engineer. The lake will be drained every summer to prevent mosquitos from 
breeding in it. LAWRENCE K. HO / Los Angeles Times 
</P>
</GRAPHIC>
