<HEADLINE>
<P>
MOYNIHAN'S PLAN TO CUT PAYROLL TAX 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Anyone having faith in the integrity of a government trust fund probably still 
believes in the tooth fairy. 
</P>
<P>
A government trust fund is an accounting procedure that transfers money from 
the government's left pocket to its right pocket. It is meaningless. 
</P>
<P>
We either trust our government to live up to its obligations or we don't. A 
trust fund won't make the difference. 
</P>
<P>
The payroll tax is a revenue-raising tax like any other tax and we should stop 
kidding ourselves that it is different because it is earmarked for a special 
purpose. 
</P>
<P>
And why it stops at an arbitrary figure like $51,300 is something that has 
never been properly explained. 
</P>
<P>
ERNST JACOBI 
</P>
<P>
