<HEADLINE>
<P>
LANCASTER MAN SLAIN IN FRONT OF RESTAURANT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 30-year-old Lancaster man was shot and killed in front of a restaurant, and 
investigators were looking for two suspects, the Los Angeles County Sheriff's 
Department reported Friday. 
</P>
<P>
The victim, whose identity was not released until his family could be located, 
was killed at 9:20 p.m. Thursday in front of Seven Brothers restaurant in the 
4200 block of Sierra Highway, Deputy Roger Hom said. 
</P>
<P>
The motive for the slaying was unknown. 
</P>
<P>
"We don't know what caused the shooting or what the relationship was between 
the victim and the suspects," Hom said. 
</P>
<P>
Deputies were looking for two men believed to be in their early 20s who fled 
from the shooting in a 1967 or 1968 Plymouth Barracuda that was yellow with a 
black vinyl top. 
