<HEADLINE>
<P>
MOYNIHAN'S PLAN TO CUT PAYROLL TAX 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Coming through the revolving door of deception now is President Bush's 
deja-voodoo economics. 
</P>
<P>
He supports the shifting of surplus payroll tax revenue from the Social 
Security fund where it belongs, to the federal budget, where it doesn't -- a 
transparent fraud against low- and middle-income employees. 
</P>
<P>
Let's have no more accusing elderly Social Security recipients of robbing 
younger workers. 
</P>
<P>
Moynihan's "pay-as-you-go" proposal is the right and honest way to go. 
</P>
<P>
PAULINE ROSS 
</P>
<P>
Sherman Oaks 
</P>
