<TEXT>
<P>
One of four suspects who escaped last month from an extradition agency's 
station wagon near Gorman was recaptured Friday in Pueblo, Colo., the Los 
Angeles County Sheriff's Department reported. 
</P>
<P>
David Allen Jeffrey, 30, was in custody at the Pueblo sheriff's jail awaiting 
extradition to California to face charges of armed robbery, grand theft auto, 
and assault with a deadly weapon, Deputy George Ducoulombier said. 
</P>
<P>
Jeffrey escaped Dec. 28 after another prisoner in the station wagon feigned 
illness and pointed a shotgun at the driver after he stopped the car on a 
freeway off-ramp, authorities said. The prisoners handcuffed the driver and his 
wife to a telephone pole and drove off in the station wagon. 
</P>
<P>
