<HEADLINE>
<P>
PBS BROADCAST OF AN ISRAELI VIEW OF INTIFADA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In his Jan. 16 review of the documentary "A Search for Solid Ground: The 
Intifada Through Israeli Eyes," Howard Rosenberg announces that his suspicions 
have been confirmed: "PBS has a pro-Jewish double standard" concerning the 
intifada. 
</P>
<P>
It is not that he finds the film unbalanced; indeed he finds it "more balanced" 
than the controversial "Days of Rage." 
</P>
<P>
In fact, Rosenberg praises "A Search," acknowledging the program's quality is 
not at issue -- a point that doesn't stop him from drawing gratuitous parallels 
between Israel and South Africa or the Soviet Union. 
</P>
<P>
According to Rosenberg, the proof of PBS' "pro-Jewish double standard" is that 
"A Search" is accompanied by a 30-minute panel discussion, unlike the 60-minute 
wrap-around of "Days of Rage." 
</P>
<P>
JERRY SHAPIRO, Anti-Defamation League, Associate Director, Los Angeles 
</P>
</TEXT>
