<HEADLINE>
<P>
LATC FUNDING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Re Councilman Zev Yaroslavsky's opposition to continuation of major city 
subsidies for the Los Angeles Theatre Center, quoted in "Stage Watch" on Jan. 
11: 
</P>
<P>
Mr. Yaroslavasky: How about a half-cent arts tax on corporate earnings in Los 
Angeles to fund the theaters? How about collecting the outstanding major 
pollution infraction fines and earmarking them to fund the theaters? How about 
suggesting alternative measures to fund the theaters? 
</P>
<P>
Yes, there are people sleeping in the streets, but funds to help them should 
not come from the arts and culture budgets. Theaters enhance the quality of 
life; LATC is one of L.A.'s few professional theaters. We need more, not less. 
</P>
<P>
DAVID ELLENSTEIN, Los Angeles 
</P>
