<P>
COMMUNIST FOES PROPOSE COALITION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Opposition groups agreed to join the beleaguered Communist government if East 
German Prime Minister Hans Modrow and his Cabinet agree to deactivate their 
party memberships until the May 6 elections. Modrow indicated that he is 
willing to discuss the proposal at negotiations scheduled for Monday. The 
proposal came from an all-day meeting in East Berlin of more than a dozen 
opposition groups after a party allied with the Communists threatened to pull 
out of the government. 
</P>
