<P>
CHURCHES CHARGED IN GAY ORDINATIONS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Formal disciplinary charges have been lodged against two Lutheran congregations 
that violated denominational policy by ordaining three gay ministers who refuse 
to renounce sexual relations. St. Francis and First United churches face 
punishment ranging from censure to expulsion from the church organization for 
"willfully disregarding" membership requirements of the 5.2-million-member 
Evangelical Lutheran Church in America. Jeff Johnson, 27, was installed Sunday 
as assistant pastor at First United. 
</P>
<P>
At the same time, Ruth Frost, 42, and Phyllis Zillhart, 32, were installed at 
St. Francis, near the predominantly gay Castro neighborhood. The ELCA bans 
ordination of "self-avowed, practicing homosexuals." A consultation team will 
be named to meet with the congregations. If the group cannot resolve the 
dispute, a 12-member disciplinary committee will review the charges. 
</P>
</TEXT>
