<HEADLINE>
<P>
ARGENTINE AIDE SWORN IN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Former Sen. Humberto Romero was sworn in Friday as Argentina's defense 
minister, two days after his predecessor, Italo A. Luder, resigned in a policy 
dispute with the army chief of staff. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
