<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: IT'S A STEAL: THIEF: DRIVES THROUGH 
DEALER'S WINDOW 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A car thief sneaked into the showroom of a downtown Los Angeles car dealership, 
revved up an expensive car, smashed it through the plate glass window and was 
last seen heading for the Harbor Freeway, authorities said Friday. 
</P>
<P>
An expensive Mercedes Benz or customized Nissan costing as much as $40,000 was 
missing from the showroom of Downtown L.A. Motors at 598 W. 18th St., Lt. Paul 
Pesqueira said. An inventory in progress was the reason for the uncertainty 
over the type of car. 
</P>
<P>
The break-in occurred after 11 p.m. Thursday. "He got into a new car in the 
showroom, drove through the front glass sliding door and over the curb," 
Pesqueira said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
