<HEADLINE>
<P>
WOMAN KILLED CROSSING LANES NEAR U.S. BORDER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A Mexican woman was struck by a car and killed while crossing the freeway near 
the U.S. border Friday night, police said. 
</P>
<P>
The victim, 24-year-old Raquel Dominguez, was struck while going east across 
the southbound lanes of Interstate 5 near San Ysidro with her brother, 
according to a California Highway Patrol spokesman. The woman's brother safely 
made it to the freeway's center divide, but she was hit just before reaching 
the divide, the spokesman said. 
</P>
<P>
The driver of the car, a 27-year-old Chula Vista man, was not injured. No 
charges were filed. 
</P>
</TEXT>
