<P>
Plans to build an $85-million indoor sports arena in Anaheim were halted by an 
Orange County Superior Court commissioner. 
</P>
<P>
After three lawsuits opposing the arena were filed, Commissioner Julian 
Cimbaluk stayed arena plans until Feb. 14, when another hearing will be held on 
the issue. 
</P>
<P>
The lawsuits were filed by the owner of Orange Tree Mobile Home Park, adjacent 
to the proposed arena site, and by the Rams and Anaheim Stadium Associates, a 
development firm. The lawsuits claim Anaheim hastily approved the project 
without regard for its environmental effects. 
</P>
