<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: LAGUNA NIGUEL; 
</P>
<P>
CITY ESTABLISHES A SPORTS COUNCIL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The City Council has established a Sports Advisory Council and is inviting 
representatives of any organized sports group or team to become members. 
</P>
<P>
In addition, three at-large members will be appointed. 
</P>
<P>
All sports groups and organizations in the city are asked to submit letters to 
the city indicating their interest in membership and appointing one individual 
from their organization to serve. 
</P>
<P>
Individuals who are not members of organized sports groups may apply for one of 
the three at-large positions. 
</P>
<P>
Applications are available at City Hall, 27821 La Paz Road, or by calling (714) 
643-1610. 
</P>
<P>
The deadline for submitting applications is Feb. 20. 
</P>
</TEXT>
