<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: WESTMINSTER; 
</P>
<P>
FRY CHOSEN TO HEAD SOLID WASTE BOARD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
City Councilman Frank Fry has been selected chairman of the Orange County Solid 
Waste Enforcement Board. 
</P>
<P>
Fry, 64, was appointed to serve on the seven-member board by the Orange County 
League of Cities. 
</P>
<P>
The board is responsible for enforcing regulations at the county's four dumps: 
Olinda, Coyote Canyon, Santiago Canyon and Prima Deshecha. 
</P>
<P>
Fry is a retired Von's grocery store employee and has lived in Westminster 
since 1957. 
</P>
<P>
A former mayor, he was first elected to the City Council in 1966. With the 
exception of 1980-84, he has served on the council every year since. 
</P>
</TEXT>
