<HEADLINE>
<P>
4 ARRESTED AFTER SHOTS HIT BUILDING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
BUENA PARK 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Four young men were arrested Friday on suspicion of firing a rifle at an 
apartment building. 
</P>
<P>
No one was injured by the gunfire, which broke out about 10 a.m. at a house in 
the 8000 block of Dracaena Street, Buena Park Police Officer Sharon Parsons 
said. 
</P>
<P>
She said the youths apparently took turns firing a .22-caliber rifle, and some 
of the rounds hit an apartment complex in the 100 block of Ridgeway Street. 
</P>
<P>
Seven youths were detained and four were arrested on suspicion of firing a 
weapon into an inhabited building. 
